00:00:13.690 --> 00:00:19.100
&gt;&gt; Judy: Hi, I'm Judy Dixon,
Consumer Relations Officer at NLS.

00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:22.160
In this edition of the
BARD Express How-To Series,

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:25.700 position:56%
I'm going to cover managing devices.

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:29.920
To access the cartridges or
USB flash drives connected

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:34.960
to your computer, choose the Manage
Devices button from the Main Menu.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:38.970 position:56%
You will be presented with a list of
devices connected to your computer

00:00:38.970 --> 00:00:42.140
and the number of books
on each device.

00:00:42.140 --> 00:00:46.940
Select the button associated with
the device you wish to examine.

00:00:46.940 --> 00:00:50.740
From this screen you can access
information about the amount

00:00:50.740 --> 00:00:53.680
of available space on
the drive and the amount

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:57.950
of space currently being
used, you can verify that none

00:00:57.950 --> 00:01:02.710
of the book files are missing or
corrupted, and you can delete books

00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:06.290
from your device or change
the name of your device.

